91
00:09:58.807 --> 00:09:59.975
Reasons being?

92
00:10:00.475 --> 00:10:02.769
He's a fugitive now.

93
00:10:03.020 --> 00:10:03.854
Fugitive?

94
00:10:03.937 --> 00:10:07.065
He's currently on the run from Blackstone.

95
00:10:07.566 --> 00:10:09.401
The Interpol is out to get him too.

96
00:10:09.818 --> 00:10:12.696
I heard a rumor that he's moved to IS.

97
00:10:12.779 --> 00:10:14.448
Only when I saw the footage.

98
00:10:14.531 --> 00:10:16.658
did I find out he's actually hiding here.

99
00:10:18.493 --> 00:10:20.996
Okay. sure.

100
00:10:21.747 --> 00:10:23.040
So. anyway.

101
00:10:23.290 --> 00:10:26.209
JSS can't handle this. right?

102
00:10:30.005 --> 00:10:31.006
No. ma'am.

103
00:10:31.340 --> 00:10:33.508
Nobody can survive a gun shot.

104
00:10:33.925 --> 00:10:35.052
I'll make sure...

105
00:10:35.135 --> 00:10:37.512
Can you at least find out where he is?

106
00:10:37.763 --> 00:10:38.597
Yes?

107
00:10:39.056 --> 00:10:41.350
-I'll find him and...
-Secretary Kim.

108
00:10:42.351 --> 00:10:43.185
Yes. ma'am.

109
00:10:43.810 --> 00:10:46.063
When you hear of his whereabouts.

110
00:10:46.730 --> 00:10:47.939
take care of him yourself.

111
00:10:49.024 --> 00:10:50.108
Yes. ma'am.

112
00:10:51.109 --> 00:10:53.779
Ma'am. just give me a chance.

113
00:10:54.154 --> 00:10:56.656
He's too good to eliminate.

114
00:10:56.740 --> 00:10:59.201
If we could get our hands on him...

115
00:10:59.284 --> 00:11:01.161
-Chief Ju.
-Yes.

116
00:11:02.371 --> 00:11:05.665
Just protect our Senator.

117
00:11:06.416 --> 00:11:08.251
You let me down yesterday.

118
00:11:10.504 --> 00:11:11.338
I'm sorry.

119
00:11:14.466 --> 00:11:16.968
Senator will be down soon.

120
00:11:18.095 --> 00:11:18.929
Yes.

121
00:11:19.179 --> 00:11:20.847
Yeah. you can leave now.

122
00:11:33.902 --> 00:11:34.778
Yes.

123
00:11:35.570 --> 00:11:37.030
Yes. yes.

124
00:11:37.781 --> 00:11:39.032
Oh my.

125
00:11:43.203 --> 00:11:45.414
What's with the faces?

126
00:11:45.497 --> 00:11:46.331
She scolded you?

127
00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:50.001
Why. because of me?

128
00:11:51.169 --> 00:11:52.087
Oh. no. no.

129
00:11:52.295 --> 00:11:54.172
Ah...

130
00:11:54.256 --> 00:11:55.882
I think it is because of me.

131
00:11:59.219 --> 00:12:00.262
Relax.

132
00:12:00.846 --> 00:12:02.347
This happens all the time.

133
00:12:22.951 --> 00:12:24.453
How shameless. huh?

134
00:12:26.121 --> 00:12:27.664
We're business partners.

135
00:12:28.582 --> 00:12:30.208
let alone a married couple.

136
00:12:32.002 --> 00:12:36.131
shouldn't he at least say sorry?

137
00:12:41.011 --> 00:12:42.012
Still...

138
00:12:44.222 --> 00:12:46.099
Still. you are saddened by him?

139
00:12:47.934 --> 00:12:48.894
Saddened?

140
00:13:00.697 --> 00:13:04.493
Just take care of the handyman.
You heard how dangerous he is.

141
00:13:05.869 --> 00:13:07.329
Don't worry.

142
00:13:08.663 --> 00:13:11.249
-And...
-What now?

143
00:13:13.585 --> 00:13:14.669
It's Anna.

144
00:13:16.755 --> 00:13:17.589
Anna?

145
00:13:18.173 --> 00:13:19.299
We got her. no?

146
00:13:20.008 --> 00:13:20.842
Yeah. but...

147
00:13:22.469 --> 00:13:24.429
Something happened overnight.

148
00:13:25.055 --> 00:13:25.889
What?

149
00:13:36.733 --> 00:13:37.609
What is this?

150
00:13:37.692 --> 00:13:39.986
While she was on the run.

151
00:13:40.070 --> 00:13:41.446
someone took a picture.

152
00:13:41.530 --> 00:13:42.697
-Then...
-But.

153
00:13:43.323 --> 00:13:45.867
the person who posted this was

154
00:13:46.451 --> 00:13:48.537
-Jean-Paul Lafelt.
-What?

155
00:13:48.954 --> 00:13:50.288
Jean-Paul Lafelt.

156
00:13:53.124 --> 00:13:55.126
The designer Paul Lafelt?

157
00:13:55.961 --> 00:13:57.712
And people online are raving

158
00:13:57.796 --> 00:13:59.923
over the so-called angel of Paul Lafelt.

159
00:14:00.006 --> 00:14:02.217
They're digging into who she is.

160
00:14:05.095 --> 00:14:06.263
Don't worry.

161
00:14:06.346 --> 00:14:08.223
We'll make sure this stays hidden.

162
00:14:08.306 --> 00:14:09.224
Hidden?

163
00:14:14.646 --> 00:14:15.981
I hear it again.

164
00:14:16.398 --> 00:14:18.149
What's wrong with you all?

165
00:14:19.526 --> 00:14:20.360
I'm sorry.

166
00:14:21.987 --> 00:14:23.029
How do we stop it?

167
00:14:23.780 --> 00:14:25.198
If Paul Lafelt is after her.

168
00:14:25.282 --> 00:14:27.117
reporters. paparazzi.

169
00:14:27.200 --> 00:14:29.369
all of Europe will be after her!

170
00:14:33.498 --> 00:14:36.626
I think...

171
00:14:38.128 --> 00:14:40.422
-We can just cause an "accident."
-What?

172
00:14:41.673 --> 00:14:44.092
Anna is the only way
to control Jang Se-joon.

173
00:14:44.175 --> 00:14:46.386
If something happens to Anna.

174
00:14:46.469 --> 00:14:49.306
how will we keep him under control?

175
00:14:51.683 --> 00:14:52.601
I'm sorry.

176
00:15:04.738 --> 00:15:05.614
Yes.

177
00:15:08.074 --> 00:15:10.160
I'd rather keep an eye on her myself.

178
00:15:10.952 --> 00:15:11.786
What?

179
00:15:13.371 --> 00:15:14.831
Bring Anna. right now.

180
00:15:16.374 --> 00:15:17.459
But if she's here.

181
00:15:17.542 --> 00:15:19.377
I'm afraid that you'll be annoyed.

182
00:15:19.461 --> 00:15:20.587
It's the elections soon!

183
00:15:20.670 --> 00:15:22.380
Who cares about how I feel?

184
00:15:23.006 --> 00:15:23.840
Move it.

185
00:15:27.010 --> 00:15:27.844
Yes!

186
00:15:58.041 --> 00:15:59.125
They look alike.

187
00:16:13.098 --> 00:16:15.684
-What's the schedule today?
-Yes. sir.

188
00:16:16.434 --> 00:16:18.561
Meeting with the Parents' Coalition.

189
00:16:18.645 --> 00:16:20.689
lunch with Traditional Market Committee.

190
00:16:20.772 --> 00:16:22.232
then a press conference.

191
00:16:22.315 --> 00:16:24.150
a junior politicians meeting.

192
00:16:24.234 --> 00:16:26.653
-and then...
-Jesus Christ.

193
00:16:26.736 --> 00:16:28.780
Oh. yes. um...

194
00:16:28.905 --> 00:16:30.448
all of this is mandatory.

195
00:16:30.532 --> 00:16:31.658
Okay. okay.

196
00:16:32.784 --> 00:16:34.411
-Chief Ju.
-Yes. sir.

197
00:16:35.829 --> 00:16:36.955
You got any smokes?

198
00:16:41.209 --> 00:16:42.585
Let's stop at a quiet place.

199
00:16:43.253 --> 00:16:44.462
Yes. sir.

200
00:16:59.102 --> 00:17:00.103
Oh. Senator.

201
00:17:00.186 --> 00:17:02.105
what trouble will you get in today?

202
00:17:11.573 --> 00:17:12.449
Senator.

203
00:17:13.158 --> 00:17:14.868
There is security in the car.

204
00:17:15.285 --> 00:17:17.996
and we can trust him as well.

205
00:17:18.997 --> 00:17:20.790
-Speak comfortably.
-Oh. sure.

206
00:17:21.624 --> 00:17:23.126
Those we can trust will

207
00:17:24.419 --> 00:17:25.670
never betray us. huh?

208
00:17:28.214 --> 00:17:29.883
-Jeong.
-Yes. sir.

209
00:17:29.966 --> 00:17:32.010
Why don't you go for a smoke too?

210
00:17:34.637 --> 00:17:36.931
Yes. yes. sir.

211
00:17:41.853 --> 00:17:45.064
You know why he's so damn sensitive.

212
00:17:46.065 --> 00:17:46.983
Yes.

213
00:17:50.361 --> 00:17:51.571
What about Anna?

214
00:17:53.114 --> 00:17:54.449
She made it home safe.

215
00:17:55.784 --> 00:17:56.910
I know that.

216
00:17:58.787 --> 00:18:00.079
She's still the same.

217
00:18:00.872 --> 00:18:01.998
Still has social phobia.

218
00:18:05.460 --> 00:18:07.712
It would be nice if you could see her.

219
00:18:11.257 --> 00:18:13.384
You know I can't do that right now.

220
00:18:18.890 --> 00:18:20.517
I'm pathetic as a dad. huh?

221
00:18:25.647 --> 00:18:26.481
Chief Ju.

222
00:18:27.565 --> 00:18:28.483
Yes.

223
00:18:28.900 --> 00:18:31.319
You're also on Choi Yoo-jin's side.

224
00:18:34.531 --> 00:18:36.115
But I'm the future president.

225
00:18:37.450 --> 00:18:38.284
Of course.

226
00:18:38.701 --> 00:18:41.579
I'll be the one making you
Security Service Chief.

227
00:18:44.165 --> 00:18:47.919
Until then. you're the only one
who can take care of her.

228
00:18:50.004 --> 00:18:50.922
Only you.

229
00:18:54.217 --> 00:18:57.011
Sure. I don't deserve to
be called a father.

230
00:18:57.345 --> 00:19:01.516
and I know how much she hates me.

231
00:19:02.684 --> 00:19:05.019
But that child is the reason.

232
00:19:05.979 --> 00:19:09.023
She's why I've lived as
Choi Yoo-jin's puppet.

233
00:19:12.902 --> 00:19:15.822
So. make sure you tell that woman this.

234
00:19:17.156 --> 00:19:18.491
If the hostage dies.

235
00:19:19.784 --> 00:19:22.078
the kidnapper dies too.

236
00:19:24.372 --> 00:19:25.707
If anything happens to her.

237
00:19:25.790 --> 00:19:28.668
everything that woman's
been planning for years

238
00:19:30.378 --> 00:19:31.880
will all go to waste.

239
00:19:33.631 --> 00:19:34.549
I won't tell her.

240
00:19:36.217 --> 00:19:37.135
And Anna...

241
00:19:37.844 --> 00:19:39.596
I'll protect her no matter what.

242
00:19:49.439 --> 00:19:50.315
Thanks.

243
00:20:22.221 --> 00:20:23.306
Come on!

244
00:20:29.562 --> 00:20:31.940
The car's acting up on me too.

245
00:20:32.023 --> 00:20:33.066
Shit.

246
00:20:33.733 --> 00:20:34.567
Phew.

247
00:20:37.654 --> 00:20:39.197
You know what you're doing?

248
00:20:40.031 --> 00:20:41.115
If not. go away.

249
00:20:42.408 --> 00:20:43.785
Why don't you call insurance?

250
00:20:43.868 --> 00:20:46.120
If I had insurance. would I be here?

251
00:20:46.746 --> 00:20:47.747
Call a tow car.

252
00:20:47.830 --> 00:20:50.500
If I could afford that.
I'd have insurance.

253
00:20:51.417 --> 00:20:52.251
Sure.

254
00:21:00.218 --> 00:21:01.719
Grandpa. give me your gloves.

255
00:21:01.803 --> 00:21:03.429
You know what you're doing?

256
00:21:04.055 --> 00:21:06.057
What if you break it more?

257
00:21:06.140 --> 00:21:08.476
There's not much more to break.

258
00:21:10.395 --> 00:21:12.814
-Give me that.
-Yes. this.

259
00:21:19.529 --> 00:21:20.488
Sheesh.

260
00:21:21.489 --> 00:21:22.448
God.

261
00:21:23.199 --> 00:21:24.242
Yes!

262
00:21:27.370 --> 00:21:29.580
-Hi.
-Oh my.

263
00:21:29.956 --> 00:21:30.957
Hello.

264
00:21:32.041 --> 00:21:34.877
We could've talked outside.

265
00:21:34.961 --> 00:21:37.422
You didn't have to come all the way here.

266
00:21:37.505 --> 00:21:40.008
Oh. but you're busy.

267
00:21:40.591 --> 00:21:42.510
Oh. look. look.

268
00:21:44.012 --> 00:21:47.181
Man. this is a very bad boy.

269
00:21:47.890 --> 00:21:49.308
We must catch him.

270
00:21:49.392 --> 00:21:51.561
but we don't know where he is.

271
00:21:51.644 --> 00:21:53.479
Oh. come on.

272
00:21:53.563 --> 00:21:57.525
You should report this to a station.

273
00:21:57.608 --> 00:22:01.320
get a warrant. and
start an official investigation.

274
00:22:02.071 --> 00:22:04.198
Want me to call an officer for you?

275
00:22:04.282 --> 00:22:05.408
You crazy?

276
00:22:05.491 --> 00:22:07.744
Why would I be here if I'd do that?

277
00:22:10.121 --> 00:22:12.290
Look at me.

278
00:22:12.874 --> 00:22:15.460
This is free insurance

279
00:22:15.710 --> 00:22:17.128
that I'm offering you.

280
00:22:17.545 --> 00:22:20.089
-What?
-What do you think...

281
00:22:20.590 --> 00:22:23.843
is the probability that our Senator
will become president?

282
00:22:25.428 --> 00:22:27.430
I don't know.

283
00:22:28.222 --> 00:22:30.558
He's popular but...

284
00:22:30.641 --> 00:22:32.727
-He's an independent.
-Right?

285
00:22:32.810 --> 00:22:33.811
But...

286
00:22:34.854 --> 00:22:38.274
The higher-ups there think differently.

287
00:22:39.400 --> 00:22:41.736
Candidate Jang Se-jun won't be

288
00:22:43.362 --> 00:22:46.491
independent for long.

289
00:22:47.075 --> 00:22:47.909
He's joining...

290
00:22:49.744 --> 00:22:51.329
This is a secret.

291
00:22:54.040 --> 00:22:57.293
Now. what do you think the probability is?

292
00:22:58.628 --> 00:23:01.047
Popularity plus an organization.

293
00:23:11.057 --> 00:23:15.770
Don't you want this insurance?

294
00:23:18.272 --> 00:23:19.440
How can I help you?

295
00:23:48.136 --> 00:23:49.679
Wait. wait.

296
00:23:50.429 --> 00:23:52.932
Stay still. Be careful.

297
00:23:53.933 --> 00:23:54.767
Okay.

298
00:23:55.309 --> 00:23:56.519
-Go.
-Got a lawnmower?

299
00:23:57.186 --> 00:23:58.521
-Lawnmower?
-Yes.

300
00:23:58.604 --> 00:23:59.981
What do you want with that?

301
00:24:00.064 --> 00:24:01.399
I can mow the lawn.

302
00:24:01.482 --> 00:24:03.734
I'm broke. forget it.

303
00:24:04.026 --> 00:24:05.570
No. I won't charge.

304
00:24:06.571 --> 00:24:08.239
Is it at that warehouse?

305
00:24:08.322 --> 00:24:09.407
I said don't work!

306
00:24:13.369 --> 00:24:15.496
I'll feed you as promised.

307
00:24:15.580 --> 00:24:17.915
Sleep there and head out tomorrow.

308
00:24:28.926 --> 00:24:30.094
It won't open.

309
00:24:31.470 --> 00:24:32.889
Wait for a minute.

310
00:24:33.389 --> 00:24:35.183
He'll open it up.

311
00:24:38.561 --> 00:24:40.855
We got signal.

312
00:24:44.066 --> 00:24:45.276
What you doing?

313
00:24:46.194 --> 00:24:48.613
Hurry up. you bastards.

314
00:24:48.821 --> 00:24:49.906
Yes!

315
00:25:06.047 --> 00:25:07.089
Excuse me.

316
00:25:09.800 --> 00:25:11.719
Doesn't she want a meal?

317
00:25:12.053 --> 00:25:13.638
She said don't wake her up.

318
00:25:13.721 --> 00:25:15.139
I see.

319
00:25:15.223 --> 00:25:17.183
Had too much to drink.

320
00:25:17.808 --> 00:25:19.894
I see. Enjoy your flight.

321
00:26:04.313 --> 00:26:05.273
Anna. get dressed.

322
00:26:07.066 --> 00:26:08.192
Dad's waiting for you.

323
00:26:25.501 --> 00:26:26.669
My dad?

324
00:26:29.380 --> 00:26:31.090
Drink. it's for motion sickness.

325
00:26:31.632 --> 00:26:32.758
And Dad?

326
00:26:34.010 --> 00:26:35.511
If you drink this. he'll come.

327
00:26:36.137 --> 00:26:37.138
You're lying.

328
00:26:39.181 --> 00:26:41.183
Yes. I'm lying.

329
00:26:41.767 --> 00:26:43.978
Your dad is not coming.

330
00:26:44.645 --> 00:26:47.606
I want my dad. Take me to him.

331
00:27:40.743 --> 00:27:43.496
I'm sorry. that's all.

332
00:27:45.414 --> 00:27:47.166
We barely get by.

333
00:27:48.876 --> 00:27:49.710
I'm fine.

334
00:27:57.343 --> 00:27:58.511
I'm sorry

335
00:27:59.220 --> 00:28:00.721
for lashing out.

336
00:28:17.905 --> 00:28:19.156
I found it.

337
00:28:19.990 --> 00:28:21.826
Where is he?

338
00:28:23.327 --> 00:28:24.203
Here.

339
00:28:24.995 --> 00:28:27.039
-When was this?
-This morning.

340
00:28:27.123 --> 00:28:29.333
But he disappeared after the bathroom.

341
00:28:31.127 --> 00:28:32.795
He changed his clothes.

342
00:28:33.629 --> 00:28:36.424
Track everyone here.

343
00:28:36.757 --> 00:28:37.675
Yes. sir!

344
00:28:41.887 --> 00:28:43.889
Come on.

345
00:28:44.223 --> 00:28:46.434
Save me. please.

346
00:32:33.494 --> 00:32:34.912
You want a sip?

347
00:32:45.756 --> 00:32:48.342
We held a ritual for our dead son.

348
00:32:49.760 --> 00:32:52.012
We were on our way from the temple.

349
00:33:11.573 --> 00:33:14.284
Fruits are like children.

350
00:33:14.868 --> 00:33:16.829
Without a guardian.

351
00:33:17.955 --> 00:33:19.289
they end up like this.

352
00:33:20.040 --> 00:33:22.042
We're closing it.

353
00:33:22.418 --> 00:33:24.169
The owner's never coming back.

354
00:33:24.253 --> 00:33:27.631
I'll cut them all and set them on fire.

355
00:33:50.654 --> 00:33:51.488
Hey.

356
00:33:52.906 --> 00:33:55.576
Can you cut these for me?

357
00:34:00.414 --> 00:34:02.207
-You sure?
-Yes.

358
00:34:02.708 --> 00:34:04.460
Rip it down.

359
00:34:05.210 --> 00:34:06.044
I can't do it

360
00:34:08.046 --> 00:34:09.256
with my hands.

361
00:34:13.969 --> 00:34:14.803
Yes. sir.

362
00:34:16.764 --> 00:34:17.598
Right.

363
00:34:18.223 --> 00:34:21.143
I feel much better.

364
00:34:21.935 --> 00:34:24.938
Help me out tomorrow.

365
00:34:25.481 --> 00:34:27.733
I'll pay you in cash.

366
00:34:31.653 --> 00:34:33.030
I'm so happy.

367
00:34:33.781 --> 00:34:35.616
I feel so good!

368
00:34:36.492 --> 00:34:37.326
Come on!

369
00:34:49.505 --> 00:34:51.632
Come on. come on. come on!

370
00:34:51.965 --> 00:34:53.634
Good luck!

371
00:34:53.717 --> 00:34:54.927
Oh. good. good!

372
00:34:55.010 --> 00:34:56.553
We need to catch him.

373
00:34:56.637 --> 00:34:58.222
You get tired. huh?

374
00:34:58.305 --> 00:35:02.601
Just try a little harder. huh?

375
00:35:33.924 --> 00:35:35.008
Yes.

376
00:35:36.844 --> 00:35:39.263
Chop them down!

377
00:36:59.801 --> 00:37:01.595
President! President!

378
00:37:03.347 --> 00:37:04.348
We found him.

379
00:37:06.058 --> 00:37:08.602
You found him?

380
00:37:31.166 --> 00:37:34.419
You can stay for longer if you want.

381
00:37:37.089 --> 00:37:40.133
If you insist. I will.

382
00:37:47.391 --> 00:37:49.101
-It's good.
-Yes.

383
00:37:53.146 --> 00:37:55.983
It's a dead man's clothes.

384
00:37:56.066 --> 00:37:57.651
If you're not bothered.

385
00:37:58.485 --> 00:38:00.779
you can wear these.

386
00:38:07.744 --> 00:38:09.079
Oh. perfect for me.

387
00:38:12.124 --> 00:38:12.958
Thank you.

388
00:38:33.145 --> 00:38:33.979
Grandpa.

389
00:38:36.023 --> 00:38:38.025
-Got more blades?
-No.

390
00:38:38.316 --> 00:38:39.526
I'll go buy one.

391
00:39:22.360 --> 00:39:23.779
Is she alright?

392
00:39:23.862 --> 00:39:26.156
No. no. just had a lot to drink.

393
00:39:27.908 --> 00:39:28.992
Call me if you need me.

394
00:40:12.119 --> 00:40:12.953
No.

395
00:40:13.370 --> 00:40:15.288
What are you doing?

396
00:40:20.043 --> 00:40:22.879
Now. let me ask you again.

397
00:40:28.135 --> 00:40:29.219
Where is this guy?

398
00:40:29.886 --> 00:40:30.762
I don't know!

399
00:40:31.596 --> 00:40:33.390
He left this morning.

400
00:40:37.727 --> 00:40:38.562
I see.

401
00:40:39.771 --> 00:40:40.814
I have no choice.

402
00:40:45.777 --> 00:40:46.945
What. what are you doing?

403
00:40:48.363 --> 00:40:50.282
Oh. no. no. no. no!

404
00:40:50.866 --> 00:40:52.868
Don't do this. don't do this!

405
00:41:01.793 --> 00:41:02.627
Please!

406
00:41:03.378 --> 00:41:04.254
No!

407
00:41:04.838 --> 00:41:06.548
No. no. no. no!

408
00:41:07.382 --> 00:41:08.508
Stop!

409
00:42:23.458 --> 00:42:24.751
Oh. my.

410
00:43:53.715 --> 00:43:55.884
Who sent you?

411
00:43:57.761 --> 00:43:59.512
I truly wish

412
00:44:00.430 --> 00:44:01.639
I could tell you.

413
00:44:04.309 --> 00:44:07.979
Yeah. they all say that.

414
00:44:10.357 --> 00:44:11.816
It's nothing personal.

415
00:44:12.776 --> 00:44:14.361
I'm just trying to get by.

416
00:44:16.279 --> 00:44:17.155
We're pros.

417
00:44:17.238 --> 00:44:19.407
I'm sorry. It's not personal either.

418
00:44:19.949 --> 00:44:21.576
I'm just trying to get by.

419
00:44:22.494 --> 00:44:23.953
You and I are pros.

420
00:44:26.081 --> 00:44:27.123
You understand.

421
00:44:32.587 --> 00:44:33.546
Even if it's not me.

422
00:44:34.881 --> 00:44:36.758
someone would kill you.

423
00:44:39.135 --> 00:44:39.969
Yes.

424
00:44:40.678 --> 00:44:42.097
I died a long time ago.

425
00:44:43.014 --> 00:44:44.307
But look. shithead.

426
00:44:44.891 --> 00:44:47.102
I understand that you want me killed.

427
00:44:48.561 --> 00:44:50.355
but I don't understand why

428
00:44:53.358 --> 00:44:55.443
you'd do that to that couple.

429
00:44:55.902 --> 00:44:56.945
What?

430
00:44:57.821 --> 00:45:01.366
You mean I tried to
kill those geezers for fun?

431
00:45:04.536 --> 00:45:07.622
Anyone who hides you will die.

432
00:45:08.873 --> 00:45:10.625
That was my order.

433
00:45:11.584 --> 00:45:12.919
So. those people

434
00:45:13.878 --> 00:45:15.630
will die because of you.

435
00:45:19.008 --> 00:45:19.843
Yes.

436
00:45:21.219 --> 00:45:23.721
You can tell me right now who sent you

437
00:45:24.514 --> 00:45:26.141
or you can tell me in ten minutes.

438
00:45:27.016 --> 00:45:29.602
I hate noise.

439
00:45:30.562 --> 00:45:31.396
Let's start.

440
00:45:43.324 --> 00:45:44.159
Who is it?

441
00:46:29.704 --> 00:46:30.538
Ma'am.

442
00:46:31.748 --> 00:46:32.916
Did you eat?

443
00:47:49.867 --> 00:47:51.035
You're all grown up.

444
00:47:53.871 --> 00:47:56.416
Pretty. just like your mother.

445
00:47:58.751 --> 00:47:59.669
Demon.

446
00:48:00.712 --> 00:48:02.380
Who. me?

447
00:48:03.423 --> 00:48:04.257
Why?

448
00:48:08.636 --> 00:48:11.431
You can't do that
to someone who raised you.

449
00:48:12.015 --> 00:48:15.310
Think about what you did to a 9-year-old
who knows nothing.

450
00:48:16.436 --> 00:48:17.604
Were you sad?

451
00:48:20.106 --> 00:48:20.940
I see.

452
00:48:22.817 --> 00:48:24.694
But you need to understand.

453
00:48:25.236 --> 00:48:29.073
I did it for you and your father

454
00:48:31.409 --> 00:48:32.744
I remember it all now.

455
00:48:33.828 --> 00:48:35.371
Mom didn't kill herself.

456
00:48:55.933 --> 00:48:57.560
Yes.

457
00:49:02.315 --> 00:49:04.233
Why didn't you just become a nun?

458
00:49:20.750 --> 00:49:21.584
Yes.

459
00:49:22.960 --> 00:49:24.629
I don't think you can eat.

460
00:49:26.506 --> 00:49:27.382
Pity. huh?

461
00:49:28.049 --> 00:49:30.134
I won't be able to see you eat

462
00:49:30.718 --> 00:49:32.804
when I cooked a wonderful meal.

463
00:49:34.931 --> 00:49:37.600
She doesn't want to eat yet. Send it up.

464
00:49:38.101 --> 00:49:38.935
Yes. ma'am.

465
00:50:37.118 --> 00:50:38.119
Oh my God!

466
00:50:38.911 --> 00:50:40.371
You surprised me!

467
00:50:44.584 --> 00:50:45.752
Wow.

468
00:50:47.253 --> 00:50:49.046
More handsome than I thought.

469
00:50:50.298 --> 00:50:51.591
The handyman. right?

470
00:50:54.218 --> 00:50:56.471
I thought you'd look more burly.

471
00:50:58.598 --> 00:50:59.849
You made it in. huh?

472
00:51:01.017 --> 00:51:04.812
I didn't think you'd show up right here.

473
00:51:12.278 --> 00:51:13.362
I came to warn you.

474
00:51:14.155 --> 00:51:15.740
Me and people around me.

475
00:51:18.075 --> 00:51:19.285
Leave us alone.

476
00:51:26.542 --> 00:51:27.835
Or else?

477
00:51:28.377 --> 00:51:29.212
Or else

478
00:51:30.254 --> 00:51:32.924
Wherever you are.
I'll come looking for you.

479
00:51:33.925 --> 00:51:36.010
This first meeting is just a warning.

480
00:51:36.636 --> 00:51:38.179
but on our second meeting.

481
00:51:40.097 --> 00:51:41.516
I will kill you.

482
00:51:45.186 --> 00:51:46.479
Just like Chief Ju said.

483
00:51:47.104 --> 00:51:48.064
What did he say?

484
00:51:48.898 --> 00:51:50.733
Attacking the origin?

485
00:51:53.820 --> 00:51:55.363
He said you people learn to

486
00:51:55.988 --> 00:51:59.075
attack the origin of the attack
when attacked.

487
00:52:06.833 --> 00:52:08.709
After learning that.

488
00:52:10.795 --> 00:52:13.673
it was easy to catch you.

489
00:52:16.217 --> 00:52:17.134
I'm sorry.

490
00:52:17.927 --> 00:52:21.055
You saw something you shouldn't have
at the wrong place

491
00:52:22.223 --> 00:52:23.891
and the wrong time.

492
00:52:24.809 --> 00:52:26.102
So I can't help it.

493
00:52:26.894 --> 00:52:30.815
Is this how you love
the husband you bought?

494
00:52:37.572 --> 00:52:38.406
Love.

495
00:52:39.448 --> 00:52:40.533
How easy?

496
00:52:41.284 --> 00:52:44.412
To think I can afford to love
in a life like this.

497
00:52:45.288 --> 00:52:46.122
I envy you.

498
00:52:48.207 --> 00:52:49.542
That reminds me.

499
00:52:51.210 --> 00:52:52.461
I have a question.

500
00:52:54.463 --> 00:52:55.464
Why are you here?

501
00:52:56.382 --> 00:52:58.885
At first. I couldn't understand

502
00:52:59.927 --> 00:53:01.304
why you'd come here.

503
00:53:02.346 --> 00:53:03.931
You're a fugitive.

504
00:53:05.099 --> 00:53:07.393
You could run away your whole life.

505
00:53:10.771 --> 00:53:11.814
I couldn't let

506
00:53:14.609 --> 00:53:16.527
innocent people die because of me.

507
00:53:19.071 --> 00:53:20.072
Innocent people?

508
00:53:25.286 --> 00:53:26.746
Those orchard people?

509
00:53:27.955 --> 00:53:29.624
Didn't you just meet them?

510
00:53:29.707 --> 00:53:33.836
You're taking this risk just for them?

511
00:53:34.211 --> 00:53:36.756
That's the reason?

512
00:53:45.014 --> 00:53:46.557
You wouldn't understand.

513
00:53:48.100 --> 00:53:49.977
You forgot reasons like this long ago.

514
00:53:51.479 --> 00:53:54.649
People say when war lasts for too long.

515
00:53:54.732 --> 00:53:56.901
people forget why they began

516
00:53:59.195 --> 00:54:00.488
in the first place.

517
00:54:02.740 --> 00:54:03.908
I'm sorry.

518
00:54:05.701 --> 00:54:06.786
You're a great person.

519
00:54:08.829 --> 00:54:12.500
I wish we'd met at a better time.

520
00:54:15.419 --> 00:54:16.837
We could have been friends.

521
00:54:17.129 --> 00:54:18.130
Don't...

522
00:54:20.466 --> 00:54:21.509
mess with them.

523
00:54:21.968 --> 00:54:23.970
Orchard? They really know nothing?

524
00:54:24.261 --> 00:54:26.347
No. they don't.

525
00:54:28.516 --> 00:54:29.350
Alright.

526
00:54:31.894 --> 00:54:34.939
I feel that I can believe what you say.

527
00:54:36.273 --> 00:54:38.734
Okay. I believe you.

528
00:54:39.652 --> 00:54:43.823
But I can't let them live.

529
00:54:46.409 --> 00:54:47.284
Stop!

530
00:54:49.161 --> 00:54:50.079
This is not a toy.

531
00:54:50.162 --> 00:54:52.164
Feeling like I can trust you.

532
00:54:52.248 --> 00:54:54.625
and risking my future for your words

533
00:54:55.418 --> 00:54:57.211
are two different things.

534
00:54:58.796 --> 00:55:02.925
You'll regret this soon.

535
00:55:06.220 --> 00:55:10.057
You shouldn't have given me a warning.

536
00:55:13.436 --> 00:55:15.146
Because we will have no

537
00:55:16.188 --> 00:55:17.314
second meeting.

538
00:55:19.275 --> 00:55:20.234
Take him.

539
00:55:20.651 --> 00:55:24.113
Make it painless.

540
00:56:07.198 --> 00:56:09.366
You must be working hard.

541
00:56:14.246 --> 00:56:15.956
Hi. What are you doing here?

542
00:56:17.083 --> 00:56:18.375
Oh. some guy

543
00:56:18.459 --> 00:56:21.796
stole a motorcycle and ran off. you know?

544
00:56:21.879 --> 00:56:24.924
And someone saw
the motorcycle coming this way.

545
00:56:26.675 --> 00:56:27.968
-This way?
-Yes.

546
00:56:30.054 --> 00:56:31.597
You must be wrong.

547
00:56:31.680 --> 00:56:33.682
So I'm saying.

548
00:56:33.766 --> 00:56:35.226
if that thief did come here.

549
00:56:35.309 --> 00:56:37.603
he's pretty damn unlucky. you know?

550
00:56:37.686 --> 00:56:40.397
This is like the mouth of the tiger.

551
00:56:40.523 --> 00:56:42.274
Oh. is it that one?

552
00:56:42.525 --> 00:56:43.359
What?

553
00:57:47.256 --> 00:57:48.132
Oh. wait.

554
00:57:49.175 --> 00:57:50.926
Give me the number.

555
00:57:51.802 --> 00:57:52.678
Hold on.

556
00:57:54.305 --> 00:57:55.639
Yes. 3812.

557
00:57:56.098 --> 00:57:59.143
No. three like tree. Then eight.

558
00:57:59.226 --> 00:58:02.396
And one and two. 3812. Got it.

559
00:58:04.523 --> 00:58:05.691
You sure?

560
00:58:06.901 --> 00:58:09.695
It is the stolen motorcycle.

561
00:58:09.778 --> 00:58:10.654
You see?

562
00:58:37.306 --> 00:58:40.059
What happened here?

563
00:58:40.142 --> 00:58:41.560
Nothing!

564
00:59:06.001 --> 00:59:08.254
No. no. something happened.

565
00:59:11.715 --> 00:59:13.217
A rat in the garage.

566
00:59:13.717 --> 00:59:15.678
Come and get him. okay?

567
00:59:15.970 --> 00:59:17.346
There's a rat?

568
00:59:18.389 --> 00:59:19.306
That's a problem.

569
00:59:19.515 --> 00:59:21.100
Go now. huh?

570
00:59:21.350 --> 00:59:22.476
Go?

571
00:59:23.269 --> 00:59:26.397
No. I have to preserve the place of crime.

